<article id=3D"content" role=3D"main">

<!-- #BeginEditable "Body" -->=20


<h1 class=3D"center">Rounding Numbers</h1>=20


<h2>What is "Rounding" ?</h2>=20

<p>Rounding means making a number <b>simpler</b> but keeping its value clos=
e to what it was.</p>=20
<p><i> The result is less accurate, but easier to use.</i></p>=20

<div class=3D"example">=20
	<p class=3D"floatRt"><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/numbers/images=
/round-70s.svg" alt=3D"round 73 is 70, 76 is 80" height=3D"78" width=3D"164=
"></p>=20
	<p>Example: <b>73</b> rounded to the nearest ten is <b>70</b>, because 73 =
is closer to 70 than to 80. But 76 goes <b>up</b> to 80.</p>=20
</div>=20


<h2>Common Method</h2>=20

<p>There are <a href=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/numbers/rounding-methods=
.html">several different methods for rounding</a>. Here we look at the <b>c=
ommon method</b>, the one used by most people:</p>=20
<p class=3D"center larger">"5 or more rounds up"</p>

<p>First some examples (explanations follow):</p>=20

<iframe scrolling=3D"no" style=3D"width: 360px; height: 210px; border: 2px =
solid rgb(238, 255, 255); border-radius: 23px; display: block; margin: auto=
;"></iframe>=20

<div class=3D"gap"></div>

<iframe scrolling=3D"no" style=3D"width: 360px; height: 210px; border: 2px =
solid rgb(238, 255, 255); border-radius: 23px; display: block; margin: auto=
;"></iframe>=20


<h2>How to Round Numbers</h2>=20

<ul>=20
	<li>Decide which is the last digit to <b>keep</b></li>=20
	<li>Leave it the same if the <b>next digit</b> is less than 5 (this is cal=
led <i>rounding down</i>)</li>=20
	<li>But increase it by 1 if the next digit is 5 or more (this is called <i=
>rounding up</i>)</li>=20
</ul>=20

<div class=3D"example">=20
	<h3>Example: Round 74 to the nearest 10</h3>=20

	<ul>=20
		<li>We want to keep the "7" (it is in the 10s position)</li>=20
		<li>The next digit is "4" which is less than 5, so no change is needed to=
 "7"</li>=20
	</ul>=20
	<p><b>Answer: 70</b></p>=20
	<p>(74 gets "rounded down")</p>=20
	</div>

<div class=3D"example">=20
	<h3>Example: Round 86 to the nearest 10</h3>=20

	<ul>=20
		<li>We want to keep the "8"</li>=20
		<li>The next digit is "6" which is 5 or more, so increase the "8" by 1 to=
 "9"</li>=20
	</ul>=20
	<p><b>Answer: 90</b></p>=20
	<p>(86 gets "rounded up")</p>=20
	</div>

<p>When the first digit <b>removed</b> is 5 or more, increase the last digi=
t <b>remaining</b> by 1.</p>=20


<h2>Why does 5 go up ?</h2>=20

<p>5 is in the middle ... so we <b>could</b> go up or down. But we need a m=
ethod that everyone agrees to.</p>=20
<p class=3D"center">Think about sport: we should have the same number of pl=
ayers on each team, right?</p>

	<table style=3D"border: 0; margin:auto;">
		<tbody><tr>
			<td><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/images/soccer-teams.jpg" alt=
=3D"soccer teams" height=3D"86" width=3D"209"></td>
			<td>=20
<ul>=20
	<li>0, 1, 2, 3 and 4 are on team "down"</li>=20
	<li>5, 6, 7, 8 and 9 are on team "up"</li>=20
</ul></td>
		</tr>
	</tbody></table>=20
<p><i>And that is the "common" method of rounding.</i> Read about <a href=
=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/numbers/rounding-methods.html">other methods=
 of rounding</a>.</p>=20
<p class=3D"fun">A farmer counted 87 cows in the field, but when he rounded=
 them up he had 90.</p>=20


<h2>Rounding Decimals</h2>=20

<p>First work out which number will be left when we finish.</p>=20
<ul>=20
	<li>Rounding to <b>tenths</b> means to leave <b>one number</b> after the d=
ecimal point</li>=20
	<li>Rounding to <b>hundredths</b> means to leave <b>two numbers</b> after =
the decimal point</li>=20
	<li>and so on</li>=20
</ul>=20

<div class=3D"example">=20
	<h3>3,1416 rounded to hundredths is 3,14</h3>=20

	<p class=3D"center">as the next digit (1) is less than 5</p>=20
</div>=20

<div class=3D"example">=20
	<h3>3,1416 rounded to thousandths is 3,142</h3>=20

	<p class=3D"center">as the next digit (6) is more than 5</p>=20
</div>=20

<div class=3D"example">=20
	<h3>1,2735 rounded to tenths is 1,3</h3>=20

	<p class=3D"center">as the next digit (7) is 5 or more</p>=20
</div>=20

<p>To round to "so many decimal places" count that many digits from the dec=
imal point:</p>=20

<div class=3D"example">=20
	<h3>1,2735 rounded to 3 decimal places is 1,274</h3>=20

	<p class=3D"center">as the next digit (5) is 5 or more</p>=20
</div>=20


<h2>Rounding Whole Numbers</h2>=20

<p>We may want to round to tens, hundreds, and so on, In this case we repla=
ce the removed digits with zero.</p>=20

<div class=3D"example">=20
	<h3>134,9 rounded to tens is 130</h3>=20

	<p class=3D"center">as the next digit (4) is less than 5</p>=20
</div>=20

<div class=3D"example">=20
	<h3>12.690 rounded to thousands is 13.000</h3>=20

	<p class=3D"center">as the next digit (6) is 5 or more</p>=20
</div>=20

<div class=3D"example">=20
	<h3>15,239 rounded to ones is 15</h3>=20

	<p class=3D"center">as the next digit (2) is less than 5</p>=20
</div>=20


<h2>Rounding to Significant Digits</h2>=20

<p>To round to "so many" significant digits, <b>count digits from left to r=
ight</b>, and then round off from there.</p>=20

<div class=3D"example">=20
	<h3>1,239 rounded to 3 significant digits is 1,24</h3>=20

	<p class=3D"center">as the next digit (9) is 5 or more</p>=20
</div>=20

<div class=3D"example">=20
	<h3>134,9 rounded to 1 significant digit is 100</h3>=20

	<p class=3D"center">as the next digit (3) is less than 5</p>=20
</div>=20

<p>When there are leading zeros (such as 0,006), don't count them because t=
hey are only there to show how small the number is:</p>=20

<div class=3D"example">=20
	<h3>0,0165 rounded to 2 significant digits is 0,017</h3>=20

	<p class=3D"center">as the next digit (5) is 5 or more</p>=20
</div>=20

<p class=3D"center"><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/numbers/images/s=
ignificant-digits.svg" alt=3D"significant digits" height=3D"200" width=3D"2=
51"></p>=20


<h2>Significant Digit Calculator</h2>=20

<iframe height=3D"146px" scrolling=3D"no" title=3D"JavaScript Animation" st=
yle=3D"display: block; margin: auto; border: none; background-color: transp=
arent; overflow: hidden; transition: 0.6s ease-in-out; max-width: 100%;" wi=
dth=3D"100%"></iframe><div class=3D"script" style=3D"display: none;">number=
s/images/round-sig.js</div>

<p>(Try increasing or decreasing the number of significant digits. Also try=
 numbers with lots of zeros in front of them like 0,00314, 0,0000314 and so=
 on)</p>=20
<div class=3D"gap"></div>

